# Stage 5 cross-device sync (DESIGN.md §2.1, see apps/api/). Unset (the
# default) = local-only mode: this app never makes a network call for
# persistence, exactly as before Stage 5. Set to a deployed apps/api Worker's
# URL (no trailing slash needed) to enable background sync.
#
# Copy to .env.local (gitignored by Vite's default patterns) for local dev
# against `apps/api`'s `wrangler dev` (typically http://localhost:8787).
#
# PRODUCTION IS NOT SET HERE. VITE_API_URL is a *build-time* value (Vite
# inlines import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL when `vite build` runs), so it is set
# as a Workers Builds "Build variable" in the Cloudflare dashboard for the
# `ledgermain` Worker — NOT committed to the repo and NOT in wrangler.jsonc
# (wrangler `vars` are runtime bindings, which is the wrong layer — Vite has
# already frozen the bundle before the Worker ever runs). Keeping it out of
# the repo means a forker's build defaults to safe local-only mode. See
# apps/api/README.md "Deploy steps" for where to click.
VITE_API_URL=
